Bronze casting has developed in Vietnam since the Bronze age 3500 years ago. With the development of Saigon - Gia nh, many famous bronze casting villages were formed: Cho Quan (District 5), Tan Kieng, Nhon Giang, Binh Yen (Cholon), Tan Hoa Dong (District 6), Hoa Hung (District 10). A bronze product has been through three principal steps: Making a mould, casting, and cooling. It include household items or objects of worship such as: pots, trays, pans, irons, censer, statues. Today, in Ho Chi Minh City, bronze casting continue in Tan Hoa Dong (District 6), An Hoi (Go Vap), Thuan Kieu (Hoc Mon).
